>> B2: Describe how file descriptors are associated with open files.
>> Are file descriptors unique within the entire OS or just within a
>> single process?

When a process is created, the highest_fd field in the pcb struct is set to 1, 
because we already have fd=0 for the keyboard and fd=1 for the console. 
Now when this process opens a file, it sets the fd for it within its fd table 
to highest_fd + 1 (i.e. the first file opened by a process will have fd=2). 
This will happen for every process seperately so each process will have fd=0,1 
set for the keyboard and console, and will start assigning fds to opened files 
from 2,3,4,... onwards. Therefore the file descriptors are unique just within a 
single process.

